Operators

An operators are logical symbols that tells the compiler to perform certain mathematical and logical operations.

The operators available in c language are given below

1. Arithmetic operators
2. Logical operators
3. Relational operators
4. Bitwise operators
5. Assignment operators

Airtmetic operators

Arithmetic operators perform mathematical operations such us addition, substraction..etc

following are the arithmetic operators 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|Operator | Description                                                 |Example  |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| +       | Add two operants                                            |A+B      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| -       | Subtract second operant from the first                      |A-B      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| *       | Multiply two operands                                       |A*B      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| /       | Devide numerator by denominator                             |A/B      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| %       | Modulus operator returns remainder after integer division   |A*B      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| ++      | Increment operator increment the value by 1                 |A++      |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| --      | Decrement operator decrement the value by 1                 |A--      |
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

Logical operators

The logical operators are used to perform logical operations of a given function.

The logial operators are.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|Operator | Description                                                 |Example        |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Logical and operation.                                     | A && B true   |
|&&       |  If both operands are non zero the condition become true.   |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Logical and operation.                                      | A || B true   |
|||       | If any operand is a non zero the condition become true.     |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Logical not. Reverse the logigal state of its operand       | A !           |
|!        | If A is true then A changes to false.                       |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Relational operators

A relational operator is used to check the relationship between two operants

following are the relational operators 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|Operator | Description                                                 |Example        |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Check if the value of two operant are the same.            | A == B true   |
|==       |  If same it returns true else returns false.                |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Check if the value of two operant are the same.             | A != B true   |
|!=       |  If same it returns false else returns true.                |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Check if the value of left operand is greater than the      | A > B true    |
|>        | value of  right operand, if yes return true.                |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Check if the value of right operand is greater than the     | A < B true    |
|<        | value of  left operand, if yes return true.                 |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Check if the value of left operand is greater than or       | A >= B true   |
|>=       | equal to  value of  right operand,if yes return true.       |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Check if the value of right operand is greater than the     | A <= B true   |                                                      
|<=       | Add two operants                                            |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Bitwise operators

Bitwise operator work on bits and perform bit by bit operation

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|Operator | Description                                                 |Example        |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Perform binary and operation.                              | A & B         |
| &       |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Perform binary or operation.                                | A | B         |
|  |      |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Perform binary or operation.                                | A ^ B         |
| ^       |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Perform binary ones complement.                             | ~A            |
| ~       |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Perform binary left shift.                                 | A >> B        |
| >>      |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Perform binary right shift.                                | A << B        |                                                       
| <<      |                                                             |               |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Assignment operators

Assignment operators assign values from right side operands to left side operands.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|Operator | Description                                                 |Example                      |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Simple assignment operator assign values from right side   | A = B                       |
| =       |  to left side.                                              |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Add and assign operator, It add leftside value to rightside | A += B                      |
|  +=     |  and assign to left side.                                   |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Subtract and assign operator, It subtract leftside value to | A += B                      |
| -=      | rightside and assign to left side.                          |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Multiply and assign operator, It multiply leftside value to | A *= B                      |
| *=      | rightside and assign to left side.                          |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Divide and assignment operator, It divide leftside value to | A /= B                      |
| /=      | right side and assign the quotent to A.                     |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Modulus and assignment operator, It divide leftside value to| A %= B                      |                                                       
| %=      | right side and assign the remainder to A.                   |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Rightshift and assignment operator.                         | A >>= B                     |
| >>=     |                                                             |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Leftshift and assignment operator.                          | A <<= B                     |                                                       
| <<=     |                                                             |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Bitwise and assignment operator.                           | A &= B                      |
|&=       |                                                             |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         |  Bitwise xor assignment operator.                           | A ^= B                      |                                                       
| ^=      |                                                             |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|         | Bitwise or assignment operator.                             | A |= B                      |
| |=      |                                                             |                             |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------




